      "id": "i-20260702-e0bc",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-02T03:56:15.577Z",
      "route": "/log-weight",
      "description": "[bug-hunt] Logging streak is ALWAYS 0 - date format mismatch between backend history and frontend streak calc (streak chip + success-message streak never render).\n\nExpected: after logging weight on consecutive days, /log-weight shows the \"N-day logging streak\" chip and the post-save message appends \"N-day streak\".\nActual: streak is permanently 0 for every user. Backend /api/v1/weight/log-data returns daily_weight_history[].date as strftime('%b %d') e.g. \"Jul 02\" (nyu_backend/backend.py:6061,6072), but the frontend streak memo builds ISO strings \"2026-07-02\" and checks days.has(iso) (src/pages/LogWeight.tsx:316-329). No ISO string ever matches \"Jul 02\", so the loop breaks immediately -> streak 0 -> the chip at LogWeight.tsx:524 and the streak suffix at :468 are dead code in production.\n\nRepro (code-level, deterministic): log weight today and yesterday, open /log-weight -> no streak chip despite 2-day run. Verify via console: fetch /weight/log-data and compare date format vs the memo's template string.\n\nSecondary defect same feature: backend carry-forwards the previous weight into unlogged days (backend.py:6064-6074), so even with matching formats the streak would count days the user never logged. Fix should compare on ISO dates AND only count real log days (or compute streak server-side).",
      "author": "shakeebshaan",
      "tags": [
        "bug-hunt",
        "auto"
      ],
      "imagePath": null,
      "imageCommit": null,
      "imagePaths": [],
      "imageCommits": [],
      "imagePrivate": false,
      "status": "open",
      "fix": null,
      "history": [
        {
          "at": "2026-07-02T11:12:41.308Z",
          "event": "reopened",
          "note": "Is it fixed ?",
          "by": "shakeebshaan",
          "previousFix": {
            "description": "Root cause: backend strftime('%b %d') dates ('Jul 02') never matched frontend ISO strings ('2026-07-02'), so streak Set lookup always missed + carry-forward days falsely counted. Fix: backend daily_weight_history now includes date_iso (ISO-8601) and logged:bool; frontend streak memo uses date_iso and filters logged:false carry-forwards. Scoped tests: 91/91 pass.",
            "imagePath": "images/i-20260702-e0bc-fix-r1.png",
            "imagePaths": [
              "images/i-20260702-e0bc-fix-r1.png"
            ],
            "imagePrivate": true,
            "imageCommit": "b0cffc52745a135767ebda08d12a9949ba134ace",
            "imageCommits": [
              "b0cffc52745a135767ebda08d12a9949ba134ace"
            ],
            "fixedAt": "2026-07-02T04:22:44.938Z",
            "by": "shakeebshaan",
            "appCommit": "119b09d2",
            "tests": {
              "passed": true
            },
            "judge": {
              "score": 100,
              "bar": 100,
              "note": "Root cause is deterministic (date format mismatch), fix is surgical (add date_iso+logged fields, update memo filter). 91 scoped unit tests green. Backend deployed + migration applied. Both secondary defects (format mismatch + carry-forward inflation) fully addressed."
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "needsReview": false
